.TH "WEBGL_compressed_texture_etc" "JS" "July 26, 2024" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
WEBGL_compressed_texture_etc \- WEBGL_compressed_texture_etc extension
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]WEBGL_compressed_texture_etc\f[B]\f[R] extension is part
of the WebGL API and exposes 10 \c
.UR https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ericsson_Texture_Compression
ETC/EAC compressed texture formats
.UE \c
\&.
.PP
Compressed textures reduce the amount of memory needed to store a
texture on the GPU, allowing for higher resolution textures or more of
the same resolution textures.
.PP
WebGL extensions are available using the
\f[CR]WebGLRenderingContext.getExtension()\f[R] method.
For more information, see also Using Extensions in the WebGL tutorial.
.RS
.PP
\f[B]Note:\f[R] This extension is available to both, WebGL1 and WebGL2
contexts.
.RE
.SH CONSTANTS
The compressed texture formats are exposed by 10 constants and can be
used in two functions: \f[CR]compressedTexImage2D()\f[R] and
\f[CR]compressedTexSubImage2D()\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]ext.COMPRESSED_R11_EAC\f[R]
One\-channel (red) unsigned format compression.
.TP
\f[B]ext.COMPRESSED_SIGNED_R11_EAC\f[R]
One\-channel (red) signed format compression.
.TP
\f[B]ext.COMPRESSED_RG11_EAC\f[R]
Two\-channel (red and green) unsigned format compression.
.TP
\f[B]ext.COMPRESSED_SIGNED_RG11_EAC\f[R]
Two\-channel (red and green) signed format compression.
.TP
\f[B]ext.COMPRESSED_RGB8_ETC2\f[R]
Compresses RGB8 data with no alpha channel.
.TP
\f[B]ext.COMPRESSED_RGBA8_ETC2_EAC\f[R]
Compresses RGBA8 data.
The RGB part is encoded the same as \f[CR]RGB_ETC2\f[R], but the alpha
part is encoded separately.
.TP
\f[B]ext.COMPRESSED_SRGB8_ETC2\f[R]
Compresses sRGB8 data with no alpha channel.
.TP
\f[B]ext.COMPRESSED_SRGB8_ALPHA8_ETC2_EAC\f[R]
Compresses sRGBA8 data.
The sRGB part is encoded the same as \f[CR]SRGB_ETC2\f[R], but the alpha
part is encoded separately.
.TP
\f[B]ext.COMPRESSED_RGB8_PUNCHTHROUGH_ALPHA1_ETC2\f[R]
Similar to \f[CR]RGB8_ETC\f[R], but with ability to punch through the
alpha channel, which means to make it completely opaque or transparent.
.TP
\f[B]ext.COMPRESSED_SRGB8_PUNCHTHROUGH_ALPHA1_ETC2\f[R]
Similar to \f[CR]SRGB8_ETC\f[R], but with ability to punch through the
alpha channel, which means to make it completely opaque or transparent.
.SH EXAMPLES
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] ext = gl.getExtension(\[dq]WEBGL_compressed_texture_etc\[dq]);

\f[B]const\f[R] texture = gl.createTexture();
gl.bindTexture(gl.TEXTURE_2D, texture);

gl.compressedTexImage2D(
  gl.TEXTURE_2D,
  0,
  ext.COMPRESSED_RGBA8_ETC2_EAC,
  512,
  512,
  0,
  textureData,
);
.EE
.SS Compatibility notes
.IP \[bu] 2
This extension was named \f[CR]WEBGL_compressed_texture_es3\f[R] from
Firefox 46 to Firefox 51 and used to be available on the WebGL 2 context
by default \[en] this is not the case anymore.
You have to enable it on both, WebGL 1 and WebGL 2 contexts, in order to
use it.
